The paper discusses the use of Twitter as a means of measuring impact of scholarly documents, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on automated Twitter accounts distributing links to scientific papers suggests a strong connection to social media and digital libraries (cs.SI, cs.DL). The discussion of differentiating between levels of engagement with scholarly papers on Twitter suggests a connection to social dynamics and networks (cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC).
